{"id":"278692270_Applied_and_Numerical_Harmonic_Analysis","abstract":"In this contribution we give an overview and discussion of the basic steps of System Identification. The four main ingredients of the process that takes us from observed data to a validated model are: (1) The data itself, (2) The set of candidate models, (3) The criterion of fit and (4) The validation procedure. We discuss how these ingredients can be blended to a useful mix for model-building in practice.","authors":["Lennart Ljung"],"meta":["January 1998","DOI:10.1007/978-1-4612-1768-8_11","In book: Signal Analysis and Prediction (pp.163-173)"],"references":["2273033_Stochastic_and_Deterministic_Modelling","310842445_Ljung_l_system_identification_theory_for_userpdf","282707871_Nearest_Neighbor_Pattern_Classification","265620618_System_Identification","245321947_Construction_of_composite_models_from_observed_data","243763759_Theory_and_Practice_of_Rcursive_Identification","238361263_Trees_as_black-box_model_structures_for_dynamical_systems","224817276_Nonparametric_Density_Estimation_The_L_1_View","224682821_Adaptive_Frequency_Response_Identification","224389798_Robust_approximation_and_identification_in_H","223522857_Estimation_of_residence_time_in_continuous_flow_systems_with_dynamics","222930036_Identification_and_Application_of_Bounded-Parameter_Models","222466800_N4SID_Subspace_Algorithms_for_the_Identification_of_Combined_Deterministic-Stochastic_Systems","38358209_Consistent_Nonparametric_Regression","3547345_Statistical_properties_of_artificial_neural_networks","3301484_Identification_and_Control_of_Dynamic_Systems_Using_Neural_Networks","3114733_Fuzzy_Model_Identification_and_Self-Learning_for_Dynamic_Systems","3081159_Nearest_neighbor_pattern_classification_IEEE_Trans_Inf_Theory_IT-13121-27","3029349_Estimation_Theory_and_Uncertainty_Intervals_Evaluation_in_Presence_of_Unknown_But_Bounded_Errors_Linear_Families_of_Models_and_Estimators","3028582_System_Identification_via_Membership_Set_